Execution Context is the environment where JavaScript code is evaluated and executed.
There are three Execution context :-
1. Global Execution Context (GEC): This is the default context. It creates two things for you: the window object (in browsers) and the this keyword.
                                   There is only one GEC in a program.

2. Function Execution Context (FEC): Created every time a function is invoked (called), not when it is defined. Each function call gets its own unique context.
3. Eval Execution Context: Created inside an eval function (rarely used due to security risks).


There are two phases of the execution context:-
Memory Creation Phase (Creation Phase) 
Code Execution Phase

For Every function call or function invokation a new context execution is created 

